Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) evaluation metrics are used to assess how well these models generate accurate and contextually relevant responses. Key metrics include: 1. Faithfulness: Ensures the generated answer is factually correct and grounded in the provided context. 2. Answer Relevance: Evaluates whether the answer appropriately addresses the question. 3. Context Relevance: Assesses the usefulness and relevance of the retrieved context in answering the question. Evaluation frameworks like RAGAS and G-Eval apply these metrics. RAGAS focuses on faithfulness, answer relevance, and context relevance using predefined prompts. G-Eval, used for Natural Language Generation tasks, emphasizes coherence and conciseness. Additionally, Auto CoT (Chain of Thought) aids by focusing on logical flow and structure.

